---
import MarketingLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';

const launchSteps = [
  ['Intake', '1-2 business days', 'Business details, services, audience, proof points, photos, copy readiness, and desired calls to action.'],
  ['Draft', '5-8 business days', 'A complete first version with page flow, copy structure, visual direction, and responsive layout.'],
  ['Review', '2-4 business days', 'One focused revision round to correct facts, tighten wording, adjust images, and refine conversion details.'],
  ['Launch', '1-2 business days', 'Static deployment, final checks, and handoff details for the live site.'],
  ['Care', 'Monthly', 'Optional support for small update batches, photo swaps, seasonal content, and ongoing improvements.'],
];

const copySteps = [
  ['Gather raw material', 'Bring current copy, rough notes, service lists, reviews, photos, brochures, or honest answers to intake questions.'],
  ['Interview or intake form', 'If the message is not clear yet, we use a guided form or short interview to pull out the useful details.'],
  ['Draft copy', 'Homepage messaging, service descriptions, FAQs, trust points, and calls to action are shaped into plain-English website copy.'],
  ['Client fact-check', 'You review the draft for accuracy before launch, especially claims, licenses, guarantees, service areas, and proof.'],
  ['Final polish', 'Copy is tightened for clarity, tone, local search structure, and placement before the build is finalized.'],
];
---
<MarketingLayout title="Process | FrontDoor Web Co." description="The professional website launch process from intake to care.">
  <section class="content-section"><div class="container prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Process</p>
    <h1>From intake to launch without dragging the project out.</h1>
    <p>The process is intentionally simple: gather the right inputs, produce a strong first draft, revise once with focus, launch, then improve through care if needed.</p>
  </div></section>
  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container timeline-list timeline-list--wide">
      {launchSteps.map(([title, timing, description], index) => (
        <article><span>0{index + 1}</span><strong>{title}</strong><em>{timing}</em><p>{description}</p></article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container comparison-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Keeping momentum</p>
      <h2>Launch speed depends on clear inputs and timely approvals.</h2>
      <p class="comparison-intro">A standard launch is usually 7-14 business days after core assets and answers are ready. Delays in photos, copy review, approvals, fact-checking, or new direction will move the launch date.</p>
      <div class="comparison-grid">
        <article class="comparison-card">
          <h3>Client responsibilities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide accurate business facts and service details</li>
            <li>Send photos, reviews, credentials, or proof if available</li>
            <li>Review copy for accuracy before launch</li>
            <li>Give feedback in one organized revision pass</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="comparison-card">
          <h3>Revision boundaries</h3>
          <p>A revision round means tightening the approved direction: correcting facts, adjusting wording, swapping images, and polishing layout. New pages, new strategy, custom features, or a different design direction are new scope.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Copy process</p>
      <h2>If the words are not ready, the process is still simple.</h2>
      <p>You do not need to be a good writer. You need accurate facts, honest answers, and a willingness to review the copy before launch.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container timeline-list timeline-list--wide">
      {copySteps.map(([title, description], index) => (
        <article><span>0{index + 1}</span><strong>{title}</strong><p>{description}</p></article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
